Patient: I want to exercise but I don't feel safe in my neighborhood.

Educator: I understand. You can exercise at home. Activities like stair climbing or walking around can help.

Patient: What about going to a gym?

Educator: Gyms are great, but if it's not affordable, don't worry. You can still exercise effectively at home.

Patient: I don't feel motivated to exercise.

Educator: Try making it fun. For example, dance to your favorite music. It still counts as exercise!

Patient: But I feel tired easily.

Educator: Start slow. Even a few minutes a day helps. Then, gradually increase your exercise time as you feel comfortable.